README.md
     1Рєњ# dotenv [![NPM version](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/dotenv.svg?style=flat-square)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/dotenv) [![downloads](https://img.shields.io/npm/dw/dotenv)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/dotenv)
     3Рєњ<img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/motdotla/dotenv/master/dotenv.svg" alt="dotenv" align="right" width="200" />
     4Рєњ
     5РєњDotenv is a zero-dependency module that loads environment variables from a `.env` file into [`process.env`](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/process.html#process_process_env). Storing configuration in the environment separate from code is based on [The Twelve-Factor App](https://12factor.net/config) methodology.
     6Рєњ
     7Рєњ[Watch the tutorial](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YtkZR0NFd1g)
     8Рєњ
     9Рєњ&nbsp;
    10Рєњ
    11Рєњ## Usage
    13РєњInstall it.
    14Рєњ
    15Рєњ```sh
    16Рєњnpm install dotenv --save
    17Рєњ```
    18Рєњ
    19РєњCreate a `.env` file in the root of your project:
    20Рєњ
    21Рєњ```ini
    22Рєњ# .env
    23РєњS3_BUCKET="YOURS3BUCKET"
    24РєњSECRET_KEY="YOURSECRETKEYGOESHERE"
    25Рєњ```
      РєњРђд
    39Рєњ## Advanced
    41Рєњ<details><summary>ES6</summary><br>
    42Рєњ
    43РєњImport with [ES6](#how-do-i-use-dotenv-with-import):
    44Рєњ
    45Рєњ```javascript
    46Рєњimport 'dotenv/config'
    47Рєњ```
    48Рєњ
    49РєњES6 import if you need to set config options:
    50Рєњ
    51Рєњ```javascript
    52Рєњimport dotenv from 'dotenv'
    53Рєњdotenv.config({ path: '/custom/path/to/.env' })
      РєњРђд
   319Рєњ## Agents
   321Рєњ<img src="https://dotenvx.com/assets/img/as2/9.jpg" height="400" alt="dotenvx-as2" align="right"/>
   322Рєњ
   323Рєњ> Software is changing, and dotenv must change with itРђћthat is why I built [agentic secret storage (AS2)](https://dotenvx.com/as2). Agents run code without humans at terminals, so plaintext `.env` files are the wrong primitive.
   324Рєњ>
   325Рєњ> AS2 is built for autonomous software: encrypted by default, zero console access, and cryptographyРђЉfirst delivery that keeps operators out of the loop.
   326Рєњ>
   327Рєњ> It is backed by [Vestauth](https://github.com/vestauth/vestauth), the trusted, pioneering auth layer for agentsРђћgiving each agent a cryptographic identity so requests are signed with private keys and verified with public keys. No shared secrets to leak.
   328Рєњ>
   329Рєњ> It's what I'm using now. - [motdotla](https://mot.la)
   330Рєњ
   331Рєњ### Quickstart
   333РєњInstall vestauth and initialize your agent.
   334Рєњ
   335Рєњ```bash
   336Рєњnpm i -g vestauth
   337Рєњ
   338Рєњvestauth agent init
   339Рєњ```
   340Рєњ
   341РєњYour agent `set`s secrets with a simple `curl` endpoint:
   342Рєњ
   343Рєњ```bash
   344Рєњvestauth agent curl -X POST https://as2.dotenvx.com/set -d '{"KEY":"value"}'
   345Рєњ```
      РєњРђд
   357Рєњ## FAQ
   359Рєњ<details><summary>Should I commit my `.env` file?</summary><br/>
   360Рєњ
   361РєњNo.
   362Рєњ
   363РєњUnless you encrypt it with [dotenvx](https://github.com/dotenvx/dotenvx). Then we recommend you do.
   364Рєњ
   365Рєњ</details>
   366Рєњ<details><summary>What about variable expansion?</summary><br/>
   367Рєњ
   368РєњUse [dotenvx](https://github.com/dotenvx/dotenvx).
   369Рєњ
   370Рєњ</details>
   371Рєњ<details><summary>Should I have multiple `.env` files?</summary><br/>
      РєњРђд
   579Рєњ## Docs
   581РєњDotenv exposes four functions:
   582Рєњ
   583Рєњ* `config`
   584Рєњ* `parse`
   585Рєњ* `populate`
   586Рєњ
   587Рєњ### Config
   589Рєњ`config` will read your `.env` file, parse the contents, assign it to
   590Рєњ[`process.env`](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/process.html#process_process_env),
   591Рєњand return an Object with a `parsed` key containing the loaded content or an `error` key if it failed.
   592Рєњ
   593Рєњ```js
   594Рєњconst result = dotenv.config()
   595Рєњ
   596Рєњif (result.error) {
   597Рєњ  throw result.error
   598Рєњ}
   599Рєњ
   600Рєњconsole.log(result.parsed)
   601Рєњ```
      РєњРђд
   605Рєњ#### Options
   607Рєњ##### path
   609РєњDefault: `path.resolve(process.cwd(), '.env')`
   610Рєњ
   611РєњSpecify a custom path if your file containing environment variables is located elsewhere.
   612Рєњ
   613Рєњ```js
   614Рєњrequire('dotenv').config({ path: '/custom/path/to/.env' })
   615Рєњ```
   616Рєњ
   617РєњBy default, `config` will look for a file called .env in the current working directory.
   618Рєњ
   619РєњPass in multiple files as an array, and they will be parsed in order and combined with `process.env` (or `option.processEnv`, if set). The first value set for a variable will win, unless the `options.override` flag is set, in which case the last value set will win.  If a value already exists in `process.env` and the `options.override` flag is NOT set, no changes will be made to that value. 
   620Рєњ
   621Рєњ```js  
   622Рєњrequire('dotenv').config({ path: ['.env.local', '.env'] })
   623Рєњ```
   624Рєњ
   625Рєњ##### quiet
   627РєњDefault: `false`
   628Рєњ
   629РєњSuppress runtime logging message.
   630Рєњ
   631Рєњ```js
   632Рєњ// index.js
   633Рєњrequire('dotenv').config({ quiet: false }) // change to true to suppress
   634Рєњconsole.log(`Hello ${process.env.HELLO}`)
   635Рєњ```
   636Рєњ
   637Рєњ```ini
   638Рєњ# .env
   639РєњHELLO=World
      РєњРђд
   648Рєњ##### encoding
   650РєњDefault: `utf8`
   651Рєњ
   652РєњSpecify the encoding of your file containing environment variables.
   653Рєњ
   654Рєњ```js
   655Рєњrequire('dotenv').config({ encoding: 'latin1' })
   656Рєњ```
   657Рєњ
   658Рєњ##### debug
   660РєњDefault: `false`
   661Рєњ
   662РєњTurn on logging to help debug why certain keys or values are not being set as you expect.
   663Рєњ
   664Рєњ```js
   665Рєњrequire('dotenv').config({ debug: process.env.DEBUG })
   666Рєњ```
   667Рєњ
   668Рєњ##### override
   670РєњDefault: `false`
   671Рєњ
   672РєњOverride any environment variables that have already been set on your machine with values from your .env file(s). If multiple files have been provided in `option.path` the override will also be used as each file is combined with the next. Without `override` being set, the first value wins. With `override` set the last value wins. 
   673Рєњ
   674Рєњ```js
   675Рєњrequire('dotenv').config({ override: true })
   676Рєњ```
   677Рєњ
   678Рєњ##### processEnv
   680РєњDefault: `process.env`
   681Рєњ
   682РєњSpecify an object to write your environment variables to. Defaults to `process.env` environment variables.
   683Рєњ
   684Рєњ```js
   685Рєњconst myObject = {}
   686Рєњrequire('dotenv').config({ processEnv: myObject })
   687Рєњ
   688Рєњconsole.log(myObject) // values from .env
   689Рєњconsole.log(process.env) // this was not changed or written to
   690Рєњ```
   691Рєњ
   692Рєњ### Parse
   694РєњThe engine which parses the contents of your file containing environment
   695Рєњvariables is available to use. It accepts a String or Buffer and will return
   696Рєњan Object with the parsed keys and values.
   697Рєњ
   698Рєњ```js
   699Рєњconst dotenv = require('dotenv')
   700Рєњconst buf = Buffer.from('BASIC=basic')
   701Рєњconst config = dotenv.parse(buf) // will return an object
   702Рєњconsole.log(typeof config, config) // object { BASIC : 'basic' }
   703Рєњ```
   704Рєњ
   705Рєњ#### Options
   707Рєњ##### debug
   709РєњDefault: `false`
   710Рєњ
   711РєњTurn on logging to help debug why certain keys or values are not being set as you expect.
   712Рєњ
   713Рєњ```js
   714Рєњconst dotenv = require('dotenv')
   715Рєњconst buf = Buffer.from('hello world')
   716Рєњconst opt = { debug: true }
   717Рєњconst config = dotenv.parse(buf, opt)
   718Рєњ// expect a debug message because the buffer is not in KEY=VAL form
   719Рєњ```
   720Рєњ
   721Рєњ### Populate
   723РєњThe engine which populates the contents of your .env file to `process.env` is available for use. It accepts a target, a source, and options. This is useful for power users who want to supply their own objects.
   724Рєњ
   725РєњFor example, customizing the source:
   726Рєњ
   727Рєњ```js
   728Рєњconst dotenv = require('dotenv')
   729Рєњconst parsed = { HELLO: 'world' }
   730Рєњ
   731Рєњdotenv.populate(process.env, parsed)
   732Рєњ
   733Рєњconsole.log(process.env.HELLO) // world
   734Рєњ```
   735Рєњ
      РєњРђд
   748Рєњ#### options
   750Рєњ##### Debug
   752РєњDefault: `false`
   753Рєњ
   754РєњTurn on logging to help debug why certain keys or values are not being populated as you expect.
   755Рєњ
   756Рєњ##### override
   758РєњDefault: `false`
   759Рєњ
   760РєњOverride any environment variables that have already been set.
   761Рєњ
   762Рєњ&nbsp;
   763Рєњ
   764Рєњ## CHANGELOG
   766РєњSee [CHANGELOG.md](CHANGELOG.md)
   767Рєњ
   768Рєњ&nbsp;
   769Рєњ
   770Рєњ## Who's using dotenv?
   772Рєњ[These npm modules depend on it.](https://www.npmjs.com/browse/depended/dotenv)
   773Рєњ
   774РєњProjects that expand it often use the [keyword "dotenv" on npm](https://www.npmjs.com/search?q=keywords:dotenv).
